    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ba5d13d1_fda97516",
        "filename": "src/gpu/d3d/GrD3DAMDMemoryAllocator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 34,
      "author": {
        "id": 5065
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-21T20:07:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The \"standard\" allocation method is to create a large heap and suballocate from it using CreatePlacedResource. If there\u0027s no room, it\u0027ll create a new one. The flags control whether you stay within budget, or whether you only suballocate from what\u0027s already allocated, or whether you skip suballocation entirely and use CreateCommittedResource. I\u0027ve updated the comment.",
      "parentUuid": "4b6b4dd1_e620f0eb",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 34,
        "startChar": 6,
